Eight suspects were arrested in Port Elizabeth at the weekend after a liquor outlet in Stanford Road was robbed for the second time this month.
Police spokeswoman Colonel Priscilla Naidu said yesterday the suspects were apprehended on Friday afternoon following a car chase with police.
“Approximately 11 suspects entered the store and held the staff and patrons at gunpoint,” Naidu said.


“The suspects had previously robbed the store on October 17.”
The suspects will appear in the Gelvandale Magistrate’s Court today.
Three more suspects remain at large.


